ever see Seiren again.

98
00:06:51,458 --> 00:06:53,291
It's all right, Tomoka.

99
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:54,875
Hey! Wait a second.

100
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:56,541
What are the Special Forces?

101
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,500
And why did they kidnap Miharu?

102
00:06:58,583 --> 00:06:59,625
Yukinari...

103
00:06:59,708 --> 00:07:01,125
But they did!

104
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:04,750
Koyomi, can you please tell
us what this is all about?

105
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,333
Mhmm.

106
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,750
The Special Forces unit
is one of the branches

107
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:13,083
of the Seiren Space
Management Bureau.

108
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,333
Tomoka and I are in
a different branch.

109
00:07:15,416 --> 00:07:18,625
We investigate missing
persons cases.

110
00:07:18,708 --> 00:07:22,833
Most of the people who disappear
from Seiren do it accidentally,

111
00:07:22,916 --> 00:07:24,500
but if anyone leaves illegally,

112
00:07:24,583 --> 00:07:28,125
it's the Special Forces' job to
bring them back for punishment.

113
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:29,708
Whoa. You bring them
back for punishment?

114
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:33,958
Yes. But that sort of thing
almost never happens.

115
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:37,500
So long as a member of the
Space Management Bureau

116
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:39,791
accompanies the traveler
and watches over them,

117
