00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:06,791
and the reason that I
can now laugh freely...

259
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:11,916
it's all because...
you were with me, Miharu.

260
00:16:15,166 --> 00:16:17,041
Miharu, please don't worry.

261
00:16:17,125 --> 00:16:19,208
I'll bring you back
here no matter what!

262
00:16:19,291 --> 00:16:22,291
I'll find a way to get to
Seiren and share with you

263
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:24,000
the things that you gave to me.

264
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:28,083
I swear. I'm going
to bring you back!

265
00:16:30,708 --> 00:16:33,416
Kirie...

266
00:16:37,958 --> 00:16:41,125
That's just what
I wanted to hear.

267
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:44,833
Now be strong.
Don't you give up, Yukinari.

268
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:47,708
Send your feelings to her,
all the way on Seiren.

269
00:16:47,791 --> 00:16:51,833
You're meant to be together.

270
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:53,708
Yeah, what she said!

271
00:16:53,791 --> 00:16:55,208
I think that Kirie is right.

272
00:16:55,291 --> 00:16:57,958
All of us meeting one
another like this

273
00:16:58,041 --> 00:17:00,208
wasn't just some coincidence.

274
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:02,791
I know you'll see Miharu again.

275
00:17:02,875 --> 00:17:05,416
Yes. I'm absolutely
sure about it.

276
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,125
Right, Tomoka?

277
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:08,833
You said it! I'm gonna
see her again, too.

278
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:12,166
So she can take this
ugly thing back

279
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:14,833
and get me a Poyon magical
transformation set.

280
00:17:14,916 --> 00:17:17,458
I'm absolutely sure about that!

281
00:17:17,541 --> 00:17:18,625
Nya nya!

282
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:19,916
Thanks, you two.

283
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,583
Miharu location squad,
get to work!

284
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:25,166
[YUKINARI] Fukuyama?
[MAIDS] Yes, Master.

285
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:27,625
[KOYOMI] Goodness!
[TOMO] Cool, check 'em out!

286
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:31,000
Wait a second.

287
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:32,875
Hey, what's going on?

288
00:17:32,958 --> 00:17:34,458
Oh, Lilica!

289
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:36,666
Working at the lab
can only get us so far.

290
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,916
It's time for us
to investigate here.

291
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,458
Just leave it to the
Fukuyama Group's

292
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:44,375
world-famous scientific
investigation team.

293
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:49,000
Their brilliant minds will get
us to Seiren in no time flat.

294
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:50,875
[FUKUYAMA laughs]

295
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,416
What's this?

296
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:55,458
Spirits of the darkness,

297
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,708
strange creatures of the
Eldritch beyond,

298
00:17:57,791 --> 00:18:00,458
in the name of Lisa Fukuyama,

299
00:18:00,541 --> 00:18:04,333
I order you to create
a portal to Seiren!

300
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:05,916
What's Lisa doing?

301
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,625
If she thinks she can steal my
soul mate's heart and run away,

302
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:11,791
she's got another thing coming!

303
00:18:11,875 --> 00:18:14,458
Besides, there's that thing.

304
00:18:14,541 --> 00:18:16,500
If she doesn't tell me what
it is and which end is up

305
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:20,458
it's gonna bug me for the
rest of my natural life.

306
00:18:20,541 --> 00:18:22,333
[EVERYONE laughing]

307
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,458
Which way did they go?

308
00:18:24,541 --> 00:18:26,416
They couldn't have
gone far, don't worry.

309
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:29,500
We'll find them soon enough.

310
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:32,416
[NANAE] They're leaving.

311
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,833
Looks like we've bought
ourselves some time.

312
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:36,750
Maybe, but the
situation in here

313
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:38,791
is a lot worse than
I had expected.

314
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:43,083
[NANAE] We may not be
able to reach them...

315
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:45,541
One shot...

316
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:57,291
[MAID A] Master, we're
getting something.

317
00:18:58,666 --> 00:19:01,250
Huh? This is it!

318
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:04,583
Everyone! Seiren's
contacting us!

319
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:09,375
Maharu...

320
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:11,333
Hey there, Yukki.

321
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,625
And Chief Nanae is
with her also.

322
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:16,375
Chief Nanae, what's going on?

323
00:19:16,458 --> 00:19:17,708
[NANAE] We're in a bad spot.

324
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:19,416
So the Special Forces
took Miharu?

325
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,791
[NANAE] Yes, I'm afraid so.

326
00:19:21,875 --> 00:19:24,000
Then we have to get over
there and save her!

327
00:19:24,083 --> 00:19:25,208
[MAHARU] I'm sorry,
there's no way for us

328
00:19:25,291 --> 00:19:28,541
to teleport you
to Seiren right now.

329
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:32,208
However, there just
might be another way.

330
00:19:32,291 --> 00:19:33,416
Please! Tell us what it is,

331
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,791
and keep in mind that
money is no object!

332
00:19:35,875 --> 00:19:40,166
And if that doesn't work,
maybe my magic can do it!

333
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:44,208
Maharu, please tell us
what to do. Hurry!

334
00:19:44,291 --> 00:19:48,375
Koyomi... you might have
the same power as Miharu...

335
00:19:48,458 --> 00:19:50,458
A power passed down
from your mother.

336
00:19:50,541 --> 00:19:52,750
You might have the star mark.

337
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,041
The star mark?!

338
00:19:54,125 --> 00:19:55,333
[SPECIAL FORCES GUARDS]
Hey, they're over here!

339
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:56,875
[MAHARU]
Dammit.

340
00:19:56,958 --> 00:20:01,416
It's up to you Koyomi, you're
the only one who can do it.

341
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:03,083
[KOYOMI]
Maharu!

342
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:09,208
Koyomi...

343
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:13,375
I can't. I could never
have a power like that.

344
00:20:13,458 --> 00:20:16,583
I mean... you all know
how useless I am.

345
00:20:16,666 --> 00:20:20,083
I just get into trouble
and mess things up.

346
00:20:20,166 --> 00:20:24,541
All of this... it happened
because I wasn't careful.

347
00:20:24,625 --> 00:20:27,166
Koyo, you're wrong.

348
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:29,958
The only one who thinks
you're useless is you.

349
00:20:30,041 --> 00:20:32,208
Because the rest of us know

350
00:20:32,291 --> 00:20:35,041
there are bunches of wonderful
things about you.

351
00:20:35,125 --> 00:20:40,125
Tomoka...

352
00:20:40,208 --> 00:20:42,625
Really?

353
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:45,250
Mm.

354
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:52,291
Father... Mother...

355
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:58,916
I need you. Please,
give me your strength.

356
00:21:12,541 --> 00:21:15,041
[DAD] It's... Koyomi.

357
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:21,791
Everybody... it's time to go.

358
00:21:21,875 --> 00:21:25,666
Hmph . You don't
have to tell me twice.

359
00:21:25,750 --> 00:21:27,875
Koyomi, are you all right?

360
00:21:27,958 --> 00:21:30,375
Yes. But please hurry.

361
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:32,666
I've never done this before,

362
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:35,625
this gate doesn't
feel very stable.

363
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:37,625
It could close at any moment.

364
00:21:37,708 --> 00:21:40,000
Come on, don't get all
stressed out over that.

365
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:43,708
Even if it closes, if we can get
to Seiren and rescue Miharu,

366
00:21:43,791 --> 00:21:45,708
she can open a new one for us.

367
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:47,833
Yeah! And Tomo could
show the others

368
00:21:47,916 --> 00:21:49,958
how to get to the Space
Management Bureau.

369
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:50,958
Nya nyo.

370
00:21:51,041 --> 00:21:52,708
So don't worry about us.

371
00:21:52,791 --> 00:21:55,125
We'll be back with Miharu
before you know it.

372
00:21:55,208 --> 00:21:56,458
Right.

373
00:21:56,541 --> 00:21:58,958
Lilica, would you please
watch over Koyomi for us?

374
00:21:59,041 --> 00:22:02,083
It would be my
pleasure Miss Kirie.

375
00:22:02,166 --> 00:22:09,083
And Kosame, we'll need
you to protect her also!

376
00:22:09,166 --> 00:22:11,250
All right! Onward!

377
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:16,458
Miharu...

378
00:22:16,541 --> 00:22:18,500
We're going to save you.
I promise!

379
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,958
Yukinari...

380
00:24:00,916 --> 00:24:02,791
What? It's almost over?

381
00:24:02,875 --> 00:24:04,708
Everything has an end,
no matter what.

382
00:24:04,791 --> 00:24:06,375
Let's finish strong.

383
00:24:06,458 --> 00:24:07,375
Does that mean
that I don't have

384
00:24:07,458 --> 00:24:09,291
to be afraid of
Fukuyama anymore?

385
00:24:09,375 --> 00:24:11,583
That's what I like
to hear, Koyomi.

386
00:24:11,666 --> 00:24:13,791
It's time we showed
those friend-nappers

387
00:24:13,875 --> 00:24:14,750
what we're made of!

388
00:24:14,833 --> 00:24:16,125
Nya nya!

389
00:24:16,208 --> 00:24:19,833
Girls Bravo, Season two,
next episode, "Final Bravo!"

390
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:21,666
Don't miss it!

391
00:24:21,750 --> 00:24:23,958
Yukinari, I love you!

